    "Silicon's indirect bandgap prohibits efficient optical gain that is necessary for a laser (CW carrier) on the PIC.",
    "This deficiency requires alternative materials or methods to introduce light sources on a silicon chip, and the developments over the past decades have led to different solutions (Fig. 3) 93.",
    "The conventional technique is to fiber-attach the PIC with a laser and an isolator (Fig. 3a).",
    "More scalable approaches integrate III-V gain materials with the PIC without fiber.",
    "But an isolator is still needed if the laser cannot tolerate reflections."
  ],
